"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626534","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>The Department for Education (DfE) has made a significant contribution to the Armed Forces Covenant, co-ordinated through the Cabinet Office-chaired Covenant Reference Group, which has been attended by both Ministry of Defence (MOD) and DfE Ministers. The DfE has provided £22 million through the Service Pupil Premium to support over 73,000 children from Service families in state schools in England. At official level the MOD works closely and routinely with DfE (and Devolved equivalents) to ensure that Service pupils suffer no disadvantage in comparison with their non-Service peers.</p><p>DfE conducted a thorough analysis of the educational attainment of Service pupils at state schools in England in 2010, and levels of attainment continue to be monitored through joint working between the DfE and the MOD's Directorate, Children and Young People. The Service Children in State Schools Network provides vital support and advice for state schools in England, and both the DfE and the MOD sit on the Executive Board. In addition DfE have a permanent seat on the MOD's Children and Young People Board, which is currently chaired by Lieutenant General James Bashall.</p><p>For full details of the close working relationship that the MOD and the DfE have on this issue, I refer the hon. Member to the MOD's written evidence to the House of Commons Defence Committee Inquiry 'The Armed Forces Covenant in Action? Part 3: Educating the children of Service personnel':</p><p>http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmselect/cmdfence/586/58602.htm</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-08T15:40:16.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626534/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626534/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Armed Forces: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on what dates he met (a) Ministers and (b) officials of the Department for Education to discuss academic support for children of military personnel.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","51306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626535","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence is determined to ensure that veterans who require help are provided with appropriate support including through the Veterans UK helpline.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to the support offered to all former personnel and their families by Veterans UK, former Gurkhas and their families can utilise the support offered by the Gurkha Welfare Advice Centres based in Salisbury and Aldershot. The purpose of the centres is to assist in the coordination of benevolence and welfare for retired Gurkhas in the UK by working closely with Government Departments, Service charities and other agencies in order to support those in need. More detail can be found at:</p><p> </p><p>http://www.army.mod.uk/gurkhas/27785.aspx</p><p> </p><p>As announced in January 2015, the Government awarded £960,000 through the Armed Forces Covenant Veterans' Accommodation Fund to Gurkha Homes Limited to provide 32 homes for Gurkha veterans.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-07T16:55:07.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626535/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626535/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Gurkhas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that retired Gurkhas and their families settled in the UK have access to adequate welfare support and advice.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","51296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626536","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>The estimated infrastructure costs of the Tranche 1 Defence Technical Training Change Programme (DTTCP), the move of REME Technical Training to Ministry of Defence (MOD) Lyneham are currently £ 200 million.</p><p>I also refer the hon. Member to the announcement made by Secretary of State on 9 September 2015 (HCWS182) that the Royal Navy, Royal Air Force and Royal Signals would not be moving to MOD Lyneham.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-08T16:04:40.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626536/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626536/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","MOD Lyneham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the estimated cost is of refurbishment at MOD Lyneham for accommodating consolidated Army, Royal Navy and RAF training.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","51317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626537","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>There were 1,097 military personnel under training at Ministry of Defence Lyneham as at 2 November 2016.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-08T16:00:56.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626537/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626537/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","MOD Lyneham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel are being trained at MOD Lyneham.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","51318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626538","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>Details of how the Ministry of Defence uses the services provided by the Bank of England as agent for HM Treasury's Exchange Equalisation Account cannot be released as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p><p>Further detail on the Exchange Equalisation Accounts 2015/16 can be found at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/exchange-equalisation-accounts-2015-to-2016</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-08T16:03:02.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626538/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626538/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Ministry of Defence: Gold and Foreign Exchange Reserves","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 31 October 2016 to Question 49921, if he will place in the Library a copy of the forward purchase programme for foreign currency as at 1 November 2016.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626539","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-04","<p>Four allegations were referred to law enforcement agencies that involved the bribery/corruption of a foreign public official.</p><p>In relation to the further questions, concerning allegations of bribery and corruption, the detailed information requested will take time to collate and I will write to the hon. Member shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","51486 ; 51487","2016-11-04T11:17:35.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626539/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626539/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of the allegations of bribery and corruption his Department referred to law enforcement agencies resulted in a company being found guilty.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","51500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626540","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>There are currently eight Naval Service personnel and no RAF personnel embedded on US Aircraft Carriers.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-08T16:00:28.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626540/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626540/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Armed Forces: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel from the (a) Royal Navy and (b) Royal Air Force are seconded to work on US Navy Aircraft Carriers.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626541","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>We currently have no plans to test the suitability of the Northrop Grumman X-47B Unmanned Aerial Vehicle for operation on board the Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carriers. Defence will continue to explore a variety of options to augment the capabilities of the QEC carriers in future.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-08T16:01:31.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626541/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626541/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to test the suitability of the Northrop Grumman X-47B Unmanned Ariel Vehicle for operation aboard Queen Elizabeth Class ships.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626542","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>There is no requirement for any Royal Marines to be part of HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH's crew at the moment although there is one Royal Marine chef currently serving aboard. Operational requirements will determine the number of Royal Marines assigned to HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH in the future.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-08T16:02:04.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626542/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626542/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Marine personnel are currently seconded to HMS Queen Elizabeth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626543","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>Delays in finalising elements of electrical design and the installation of Multi-Cable Transit insulation in accordance with new legislative regulations resulted in some adjustments in the build schedule. These issues have now been resolved and Tidespring is expected to arrive in the UK in early 2017 to begin UK customisation and capability assessment trials.</p><p>Notwithstanding these issues, which are not unusual for any First of Class ship, build of the remaining ships in the Class is progressing well and we remain confident that all four tankers will be in service with the Royal Fleet Auxiliary by the end of 2018, as planned.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-08T16:05:06.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626543/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626543/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the principal technical faults are that have led to the delay of the transfer of the RFA Tidespring to the UK for customisation and capability assessment trials until 2017.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626544","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>The proportion of women employed by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) receiving Inner London Weighting, which is paid if the permanent or temporary duty station is within a five mile radius of Charing Cross, as at 31 October 2016, is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD pays an Inner London salary uplift to those whose permanent or temporary duty station is within a five mile radius of Charing Cross.</p><p> </p><p>As at 31 October 2016, the proportion of females employed in these roles was:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Civil Service Grade</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Female Proportion</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E2 (Administrative Assistant)</p></td><td><p>21.5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E1 (Administrative Officer)</p></td><td><p>50.3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>D (Executive Officer)</p></td><td><p>48.5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C2 (Higher Executive Officer)</p></td><td><p>35.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fast Streamer</p></td><td><p>31.7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C1 (Senior Executive Officer)</p></td><td><p>34.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>B2 (Grade 7)</p></td><td><p>40.5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>B1 (Grade 6)</p></td><td><p>32.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Civil Servant Pay Band 1</p></td><td><p>31.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Civil Servant Pay Band 2</p></td><td><p>21.4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Civil Servant Pay Band 3</p></td><td><p>50.0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>38.3%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes</strong></p><ol><li>Data is for staff on the Ministry of Defence Main and Senior Civil Servant pay structures.</li><li>The data for Senior Civil Servants is based on them being posted in a London location.</li></ol><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-08T15:35:19.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626544/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626544/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Ministry of Defence: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on an inner London pay structure in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","51389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626545","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-04","<p>The Ministry of Defence has spent to date a total of circa. £34.4 million on the maintenance and checks carried out by the Department and regulators on the decommissioned submarines that are awaiting disposal.</p><p> </p><p>The approximate figures for Her Majesty’s Naval Base Devonport and Rosyth Dockyard are circa. £11.9 million and £22.5 million respectively.</p><p> </p><p>The first submarine to undergo initial dismantling under the Submarine Dismantling Programme will be HMS Swiftsure.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","51442","2016-11-04T11:24:31.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626545/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626545/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Nuclear Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which submarine will undergo Initial Dismantling at Rosyth.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","51434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626546","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-04","<p>Four allegations were referred to law enforcement agencies that involved the bribery/corruption of a foreign public official.</p><p>In relation to the further questions, concerning allegations of bribery and corruption, the detailed information requested will take time to collate and I will write to the hon. Member shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","51486 ; 51500","2016-11-04T11:17:35.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626546/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626546/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2016 to Question 49700, how many of the allegations of bribery and corruption referred by his Department to law enforcement agencies involved (a) UK companies and (b) foreign companies; and if he will release the names of those companies and the results of any investigations.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","51487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626547","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-04","<p>The Ministry of Defence has spent to date a total of circa. £34.4 million on the maintenance and checks carried out by the Department and regulators on the decommissioned submarines that are awaiting disposal.</p><p> </p><p>The approximate figures for Her Majesty’s Naval Base Devonport and Rosyth Dockyard are circa. £11.9 million and £22.5 million respectively.</p><p> </p><p>The first submarine to undergo initial dismantling under the Submarine Dismantling Programme will be HMS Swiftsure.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","51434","2016-11-04T11:24:31.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626547/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626547/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on maintenance and checks for the nuclear-powered submarines in laid-up storage at (a) Her Majesty's Naval Base Devonport and (b) Rosyth Dockyard.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","51442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626548","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-08","<p>Ships' maintenance and support periods are programmed depending on a ship's requirement and as part of the long-term Fleet Operational Schedule. We do not disclose the detail of such scheduling, as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-08T15:41:46.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626548/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626548/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47824, what provisions his Department has made to service all six Type 45 Destroyers when they are alongside together at HMNB Portsmouth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626549","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-09","<p>The creation of British Defence Staffs in the Middle Esat, Asia Pacific and Africa is making good progress and is on track for establishment by the end of 2016. We are currently in the final stages of reaching formal agreement with the three host nations. I will write to the hon. Member to inform him of the dates when the British Defence Staffs will be in operation.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-09T14:44:00.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626549/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626549/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 15 February 2016 to Question 26634, what progress he has made on the establishment of UK Defence Staffs in the Asia Pacific, Middle East and Africa.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","51417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626550","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-04","<p>Four allegations were referred to law enforcement agencies that involved the bribery/corruption of a foreign public official.</p><p>In relation to the further questions, concerning allegations of bribery and corruption, the detailed information requested will take time to collate and I will write to the hon. Member shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","51487 ; 51500","2016-11-04T11:17:35.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626550/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626550/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-01","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2016 to Question 49700, how many of the allegations of bribery and corruption referred by his Department to law enforcement agencies involved the bribery of foreign public officials; and how many of those referrals resulted in law enforcement action being taken.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","51486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626551","Department for Education","false","2016-11-04","<p>Peter Lauener is currently the Shadow Chief Executive for the Institute for Apprenticeships. A permanent Chief Executive will be appointed in 2017 through an open competition recruitment process.</p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-11-04T11:44:07.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626551/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626551/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-01","Institute for Apprenticeships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to consult with employers on the appointment of a new permanent chief executive of the Institute for Apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","51490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626552","Department for Education","false","2016-11-09","<p>The attached tables show the number of adult students who started NVQ qualifications by level in each academic year between 2013/14 and 2015/16. It shows all further education providers that delivered courses in the Greater Manchester area.</p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-11-09T16:19:25.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626552/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626552/answer","51436 attachment.xlsx","51436 attachment.xlsx","Adult students starting NVQ qualifications","Adult students starting NVQ qualifications","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626552/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-01","Further Education: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students enrolled in each of the further education colleges in Greater Manchester for each level of NVQ in the last three years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","51436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626553","Department for Education","false","2016-11-09","<p>The Department cannot provide local progression data from NVQ level 2 as requested, as it does not hold the relevant data centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Destination data has been published for 2013/14 on the basis of college type and provider level. This is available in Tables 3 and 5 at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/564207/outcome_based_success_measures__summary_tables.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/564207/outcome_based_success_measures__summary_tables.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>The data shows that in England, 18% of those completing full level 2 were participating in sustained learning.</p><p> </p><p>81% of those completing full level 2 also had a sustained positive outcome (employment and/or learning).</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-11-09T16:23:00.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626553/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626553/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-01","Further Education: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students progressed from level 2 NVQ to further training and education in each of the further education colleges in Greater Manchester in the last five years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","51437"
