"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626556","Department for Education","false","2016-11-07","<p>The Department for Education and the Government Equalities Office do not have an inner London pay zone.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-07T11:42:58.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626556/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626556/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-01","Department for Education: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of women are employed by her Department on an inner London pay structure in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","51390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626557","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-04","<p>This Government believes everyone deserves to be treated fairly at work and is clear that employers must take their employment law responsibilities seriously and cannot simply opt out of them.</p><p>That is why my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister has announced an independent review of employment practices in the modern economy, which will consider how employment practices might need to change in order to keep pace with modern business models including the impact on job security and workplace rights.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-04T14:12:05.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626557/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626557/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-01","Sharing Economy: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the legal protections in place for workers engaged with online platforms in the gig economy.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","51367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626558","Department for Education","false","2016-11-08","<p>The number of children who ceased to be looked after due to the granting of a special guardianship order during the year ending 31 March 2016, is shown in the table below<sup>1,2,3</sup>.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Age on ceasing (years)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>number</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Under 1</p></td><td><p>700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 to 4</p></td><td><p>1,470</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5 to 9</p></td><td><p>1,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10 to 15</p></td><td><p>610</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16 and over</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> Source: SSDA903</em></p><ol><li>Numbers have been rounded to the nearest 10.</li><li>Only the last occasion on which a child ceased to be looked in the year has been counted.</li></ol><p>Figures exclude children looked after under an agreed series of short term placements.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-11-08T17:48:58.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626558/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626558/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-01","Special Guardianship Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many special guardianship orders were made in respect of children who were (a) under one year old, (b) one to four years old, (c) five to nine years old, (d) 10 to 15 years old and (e) 16 years old and above on 31 March 2016.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","51356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626559","Women and Equalities","false","2016-11-09","<p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission is responsible for determining its own structure and any consultation it undertakes on that. I have therefore asked the Chief Executive Officer of the Commission to write to the Right Honourable Member with the information requested.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-09T13:39:58.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626559/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626559/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-11-01","Equality and Human Rights Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, which civil society stakeholders have been consulted on the proposed restructuring of the Equality and Human Rights Commission.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","51366"
