od of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626663/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-01","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Mental Health Five Year Forward View Dashboard, when his Department plans to publish data relating to the indicator on IPS Programme spend.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","51522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626664","Home Office","false","2016-11-04","<p>Cabinet Papers are a matter for the Cabinet Office.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-04T13:24:46.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626664/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626664/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Orgreave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will release all Cabinet papers relating to events at Orgreave in 1984.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","51523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626665","Home Office","false","2016-11-11","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information which you have requested. Decisions on operational policing matters are a matter for the respective police force(s) involved and it is not common practice for their operational orders to be submitted to the Home Office or other Government departments.</p><p>As the Home Secretary told the House on 31 October, the Police &amp; Crime Commissioner for South Yorkshire and South Yorkshire Police is considering how the force’s papers relating to Orgreave should be released.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-11T15:49:57.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626665/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626665/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Orgreave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to her Answer of 31 October 2016, Official Report, columns 645-6, when the operational order of the day will be released.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","51440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626666","Home Office","false","2016-11-11","<p>Details of allowed appeals which are not being contested by the Home Office are sent electronically on a daily basis to decision making centres, which arrange for appropriate follow on actions to be taken reflecting the Tribunal’s determination in each case.</p><p>My officials are currently reviewing the arrangements for monitoring performance on follow on actions to identify the scope for improvements.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-11T15:27:04.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626666/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626666/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Immigration: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to monitor and improve the performance of UK Visas and Immigration's implementation of decisions made by the First Tier Tribunal (Immigration and Asylum).","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","51383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626667","Cabinet Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>The total cost of the Police and Crime Commissioner elections held in May 2016 comprises two main elements: the expenditure incurred by Returning Officers in running the polls; and the cost of producing and delivering on-demand candidate information booklets. Returning Officers have six months from the day of the elections to submit their expenses claims and so the final cost will not be known until all of these have been received, scrutinised and settled. The majority of Returning Officers’ expenditure was incurred in April and May 2016.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-11-08T17:13:49.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626667/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626667/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-11-01","Police and Crime Commissioners: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the (a) total cost and (b) cost in each principal category of expenditure was of the police and crime commissioner elections in 2016; and in which months of 2016 costs for each of the principal items were incurred.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","51402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626669","Cabinet Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-11-08T12:41:39.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626669/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626669/answer","PQ 51403 v.02 (1) (1).pdf","PQ 51403 v.02 (1) (1).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ51403","UKSA Response to PQ51403","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626669/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-11-01","Home Shopping: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many fraud offences involving online shopping have been recorded by each UK law enforcement agency in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","51403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626670","Home Office","false","2016-11-09","<p>The Home Office does not hold this information.</p><p>The National Police Air Service (NPAS) is responsible for the provision of police air support in England and Wales and its performance is overseen by the NPAS Strategic Board, which comprises chief constables and police and crime commissioners from each region.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-09T16:27:35.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626670/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626670/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Police: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average police helicopter response times have been for each police force in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","51404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626671","Home Office","false","2016-11-15","<p>The Independent Inquiry informed the Home Office on 28 September of concerns about Ben Emmerson’s leadership of the counsel team which did not include reference to an alleged sexual assault. It was made clear that no complaint had been made.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-15T13:14:22.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626671/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626671/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Child Sexual Abuse Independent Panel Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when her Department was first notified by the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse that an allegation of sexual assault had been made against Ben Emmerson QC.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","51399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626672","Home Office","false","2016-11-11","<p>All children arriving in the UK under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 are granted temporary admission while we consider their asylum claim. They are also referred to the Refugee Council’s Children's Panel Advice Service.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","51378","2016-11-11T15:28:54.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626672/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/626672/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-01","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what immigration status children transferred to the UK under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 will be given on arrival in the UK.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","51377"
