"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/625908","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Defence Intelligence civilian workforce has some 1,425 people, comprising 915 men (64%) and 510 women (36%).</p><p>Recording ethnicity across the Department is voluntary and within Defence Intelligence about 255 (some 18%) of civilian staff chose not to declare if they were from a BAME background. Those who declared as BAME number some 60, or about 5%. This compares favourably to the wider MOD figure of some 4%.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-02T16:36:16.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/625908/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/625908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/625908/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-31","Defence Intelligence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civilian staff within Defence Intelligence are (a) men, (b) women and (c) from black and minority ethnic groups.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","50996"
